cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper heavily relies on the theory and algorithms of holonomic systems, which is a topic in symbolic computation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the algorithm to the Fisher-Bingham integral, which is used in directional statistics and can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category as the paper deals with finding local maximum and minimum of a function, which is a common problem in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents a new algorithm for finding local maximum and minimum, which is a topic in algorithms. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the application of the algorithm to numerical integration on the sphere.
